WEBVTT

00:00.100 --> 00:02.029
Previously on Ghost Whisperer...

00:02.090 --> 00:04.760
Hey,you remember that time I was grinding up

00:04.830 --> 00:06.860
All the egg shells with the fake blood?

00:06.930 --> 00:08.430
For your Haitian Voodoo thesis?

00:08.500 --> 00:10.730
"Vodou." in Haiti, it's "Vodou."

00:15.100 --> 00:16.690
Forever.

00:16.760 --> 00:18.590
If you'll have me.

00:20.590 --> 00:23.660
Melinda Gordon...

00:23.730 --> 00:26.500
Oh,will you marry me...again?

00:28.260 --> 00:30.300
Yes!

00:35.560 --> 00:37.860
I thought you didn't want to do anything formal.

00:37.930 --> 00:39.500
I mean, a seating chart?

00:39.560 --> 00:40.860
Uh,would save my life.

00:40.930 --> 00:42.030
If I don't have one,

00:42.100 --> 00:43.630
my mom might have to sit next to Jim's mother.

00:43.690 --> 00:45.090
And that would be bad.

00:45.160 --> 00:46.830
Wait,your mom is coming?

00:46.890 --> 00:48.860
Yeah. She found out from one of my friends

00:48.930 --> 00:50.260
That Melinda is seeing someone new.

00:50.330 --> 00:52.430
Yeah,and if she finds out that I'm marrying this new guy

00:52.500 --> 00:54.100
And I didn't invite her...

00:54.160 --> 00:55.790
Why would you even think of inviting her?

00:55.860 --> 00:57.460
'cause she's Jim's mom!

00:57.530 --> 00:59.230
Who thinks that Jim is dead,

00:59.300 --> 01:01.690
Like most of your guests, by the way.

01:01.760 --> 01:03.230
Look,if everyone knew that I was Jim,

01:03.300 --> 01:05.030
Then we wouldn't have to get married, would we?

01:05.099 --> 01:06.990
That's obvious. Look,my brain hurts.

01:07.060 --> 01:09.360
Look,we've discussed this,ok?

01:09.430 --> 01:11.130
How can I possibly tell everyone the truth? And P.S.

01:11.200 --> 01:14.300
How long did it take you to realize that ghosts were real?

01:14.360 --> 01:16.460
Ok,you make a good point.

01:16.530 --> 01:17.790
Yes. This is Jim's baby,

01:17.860 --> 01:19.730
And Sam is just this wonderful guy

01:19.790 --> 01:21.990
Who's going to help me raise it,ok?

01:22.060 --> 01:23.400
What about Jim's mom?

01:23.460 --> 01:25.460
And Sam's, for that matter?

01:25.530 --> 01:28.060
Ok,look. We will tell my mom eventually.

01:28.130 --> 01:29.612
And Sam's mom,

01:29.612 --> 01:32.030
We'll jump off that bridge when we come to it. Don't worry.

01:32.100 --> 01:33.500
See ya.

01:33.560 --> 01:34.690
All right,I'm gonna do these errands,

01:34.760 --> 01:35.890
And then I'm gonna work on my med school apps.

01:35.960 --> 01:37.400
See ya.

01:37.460 --> 01:38.430
Good-bye!

01:38.500 --> 01:40.200
Bye! Ha ha. See ya, Ned.

01:41.430 --> 01:43.300
- How's it going?  - Good.

01:43.360 --> 01:45.130
Is that a baby bump you got going there?

01:45.200 --> 01:47.030
Ned! What is wrong with you?

01:47.100 --> 01:48.760
Were you raised by wolves?

01:48.830 --> 01:50.890
It's ok. I'm showing it off. I like it.

01:50.960 --> 01:54.360
Ok,then let me make a note of that for the dressmaker.

01:54.430 --> 01:55.930
Ned,how's the study group?

01:55.990 --> 01:58.530
We're studying, but technically we're not a group yet.

01:58.590 --> 02:00.960
Oh, Serena's not here yet?

02:01.030 --> 02:03.690
Late,as usual.

02:08.259 --> 02:09.860
I swear,I left plenty of time,

02:09.930 --> 02:11.660
But my keys,they got locked in the car,

02:11.730 --> 02:15.100
And I put them in my bag, so it wasn't my fault this time.

02:15.160 --> 02:16.200
Did you bring the chapter notes?

02:16.260 --> 02:18.790
Yeah, they're right here in my notebook.

02:18.860 --> 02:22.500
Oh, my god, where is my notebook?

02:22.560 --> 02:25.400
God, why is this happening to me?

02:25.460 --> 02:28.160
Poor Ned. He's really worried about this test,

02:28.230 --> 02:31.260
And that poor girl brings nothing but excuses.

02:31.330 --> 02:32.830
She brought a little bit more than that.

02:34.090 --> 02:35.200
What?

02:40.130 --> 02:41.560
No.

02:41.630 --> 02:43.130
I'm just saying,

02:43.200 --> 02:46.460
She might be telling the truth about it not being her fault.

